  "texts": [
    "Second, we found that the two measures of affect were significantly related to two components of engagement: popularity and polarity.",
    "Higher affective valence was associated with higher popularity, reflecting more views and likes, and lower polarity, reflecting fewer dislikes and comments.",
    "Higher affective density, on the other hand, was related to higher popularity for almost all topics.",
    "Third, we observed substantial moderation of these effects by the topic of the talk, but not by whether the talk contained scientific or nonscientific content.",
    "Our results demonstrate that affect as a surface-level characteristic of science communication on social media can impact how the public engages with scientific content."
  ],
